Description: Fragment of amygdaloid handle of a pottery transport amphora. Clay near coarse, micaceous, brown. Rectangular stamp. Greek inscription.
Curator's comments: Pencil '66' (or 99). Petrie Diary 1884-5 (EES Archive XVII 47) p. 27a, 12? Name Zenon
